<response><error><![CDATA[OK]]></error><limit>1</limit><offset>0</offset><number_of_page_results>1</number_of_page_results><number_of_total_results>1</number_of_total_results><status_code>1</status_code><results><aliases/><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/character/3005-390/]]></api_detail_url><birthday/><date_added>2008-06-08 22:12:00</date_added><date_last_updated>2011-05-05 12:19:17</date_last_updated><deck><![CDATA[Kira is a fighter in the Mortal Kombat series. She first appears in Mortal Kombat: Deception.]]></deck><description><![CDATA[<h2>Profile</h2> <b>Alignment</b><b>: </b>Evil<br/> <b>Species:</b> Human<br/> <b>Origin: </b>Earthrealm<br/> <b>Allies: </b><a data-ref-id="3005-359" href="/kobra/3005-359/" slug="kobra">                    Kobra</a>, <a data-ref-id="3005-218" href="/kabal/3005-218/" slug="kabal">                    Kabal</a>, <a data-ref-id="3005-216" href="/kano/3005-216/" slug="kano">                   Kano</a>, <a data-ref-id="3005-387" href="/jarek/3005-387/" slug="jarek">                  Jarek</a>, <a data-ref-id="3005-383" href="/havik/3005-383/" slug="havik">                 Havik</a><br/> <b>Enemies:</b> <a data-ref-id="3005-70" href="/sonya-blade/3005-70/" slug="sonya-blade">                Sonya</a>, <a data-ref-id="3005-406" href="/shujinko/3005-406/" slug="shujinko">               Shujinko</a>, <a data-ref-id="3005-235" href="/jax/3005-235/" slug="jax">              Jax<br/></a><br/><h2>Story </h2>Kira used to be a black market dealer - she was selling weapons to terrorists in an Afghanistanian mountain. She was disguised as a man. During a hard deal in a cave, her gender was revealed, and she had no choice but to fight her way out. Emerging victorious, she met <a data-ref-id="3005-218" href="/kabal/3005-218/" slug="kabal">            Kabal</a>, who had been waiting outside to observe the fight. He wanted to rebuild the Black Dragon, and after seeing Kira's epic and cold-fashioned fighting style, he was reminded of the Red Dragon, the organization from which the Black Dragon split. So Kabal offered her to make her his first recruit. She accepted.  <p>Mortal Kombat: Armageddon: <a data-ref-id="3005-409" href="/taven/3005-409/" slug="taven">           Taven</a> finds her and <a data-ref-id="3005-359" href="/kobra/3005-359/" slug="kobra">          Kobra</a> in front of a bridge in the jungle, near the Black Dragon stronghold. While Kobra stays behind to fight off Taven, Kira moves ahead to regroup with Kabal. </p><br/><h2>Endings<a data-ref-id="3030-383" href="/mortal-kombat-deception/3030-383/" slug="mortal-kombat-deception"> <b> </b></a><br/></h2><h3><a data-ref-id="3030-383" href="/mortal-kombat-deception/3030-383/" slug="mortal-kombat-deception">Mortal Kombat: Deception</a>  </h3>Kabal congratulated Kobra and Kira after defeating the enemies of <a data-ref-id="3005-383" href="/havik/3005-383/" slug="havik">  Havik</a>. However the real test for Kira was to face Kobra to prove that she's worthy of the new Black Dragon clan. Kobra was a strong and furious enemy. His lack of discipline, however, let Kira prevail and win the fight.<br/> <br/><h3><a data-ref-id="3030-11843" href="/mortal-kombat-armageddon/3030-11843/" slug="mortal-kombat-armageddon">Mortal Kombat: Armageddon</a>  </h3>Kira defeated Blaze and received god power, but in the battle, Kobra had  been slain. Kira channeled her energy into Kobra's body and revived  him. As Kobra regained consciousness, he reveled in the surge of godlike  power and prevented Kira from severing their bond. He then killed her  and stole the power from her. He felt no remorse and thought she should  have left him dead. <br/> <br/><h2>Fatalities</h2><b>Mortal Kombat: Deception</b><br/>Torso Rip<b>:</b> She throws her Dragon Teeth, two small  serrated daggers, into her opponent's feet, then struts toward her  adversary and rips their body in half at the waist, before tossing it  away.<br/> <br/>Dragon's Shotgun<b>:</b> She slices her opponent twice across  the neck, then delivers a powerful kick, which knocks the opponents head  off and sends them across the arena.]]></description><gender>2</gender><id>390</id><image><icon_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/square_avatar/8/87790/1539912-kira_bio.png]]></icon_url><medium_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/8/87790/1539912-kira_bio.png]]></medium_url><screen_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/screen_medium/8/87790/1539912-kira_bio.png]]></screen_url><small_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/8/87790/1539912-kira_bio.png]]></small_url><super_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_large/8/87790/1539912-kira_bio.png]]></super_url><thumb_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_avatar/8/87790/1539912-kira_bio.png]]></thumb_url><tiny_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/square_mini/8/87790/1539912-kira_bio.png]]></tiny_url></image><last_name/><name><![CDATA[Kira]]></name><real_name/><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/kira/3005-390/]]></site_detail_url><first_appeared_in_game><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/game/3030-383/]]></api_detail_url><id>383</id><name><![CDATA[Mortal Kombat: Deception]]></name></first_appeared_in_game><concepts><concept><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/concept/3015-96/]]></api_detail_url><id>96</id><name><![CDATA[Breast Bounce]]></name><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/breast-bounce/3015-96/]]></site_detail_url></concept><concept><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/concept/3015-2125/]]></api_detail_url><id>2125</id><name><![CDATA[Character Select Screen]]></name><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/character-select-screen/3015-2125/]]></site_detail_url></concept><concept><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/concept/3015-2198/]]></api_detail_url><id>2198</id><name><![CDATA[Hara-Kiri]]></name><